Definitions:

[command...]
	The name of the command(s) whose description and usage is required. It is an optional argument.

[-v | --verbose ]
	Verbose-mode. If used with the command-name argument, the usage and man-page of that command is printed-out.

Description:
	If a command-name is provided (without verbosity), it prints-out the description and usage of that command. If the verbose argument is used, then the usage and man-page of the command is printed. If no command-name is provided, it lists the set of commands available.

Code:

Implementing Class 
    edu.virginia.vcgr.genii.client.cmd.tools.HelpTool

